# Slack Notify (Cursor -> Slack)

When the conditions below are met, send a notification to Slack using the **cursor-slack-bot** MCP server. Messages are sent as a Bot so you receive push notifications on your phone.

## Prerequisites

- Use server `cursor-slack-bot` (not plugin-slack-slack). Channel is configured in slack-notify-config (`SLACK_CHANNEL_ID`: #cursor-notify).
- Call the appropriate tool: `notify_build_result`, `notify_task_complete`, or `ask_user_decision` (see below).
- Ensure `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN` is set in ~/.cursor/mcp.json (from api.slack.com/apps after creating the Slack App).

## When to Send

1. **Build/Test result** — After running `bazel build` or `bazel test`, call `notify_build_result`.
2. **Task complete** — After finishing a multi-step task (e.g. feature, bugfix), call `notify_task_complete`.
3. **Decision needed** — When the Agent needs user input to choose between options, call `ask_user_decision`.

Respect the toggles in slack-notify-config (SLACK_NOTIFY_ON_BUILD, SLACK_NOTIFY_ON_TASK_COMPLETE, SLACK_NOTIFY_ON_DECISION_NEEDED). If not specified, assume all true.

## Tools (cursor-slack-bot server)

- **notify_build_result** — Parameters: `target` (string, e.g. `//txm/module/canbus/...`), `status` (`PASSED` or `FAILED`), `duration` (string, e.g. `45s`), `details` (optional string, e.g. failed test names).
- **notify_task_complete** — Parameters: `task_name` (string), `summary` (string), `files_changed` (optional string).
- **ask_user_decision** — Parameters: `question` (string), `options` (array of strings, e.g. `["Option A description", "Option B description"]`).

Keep messages concise. The MCP server formats the message and posts to #cursor-notify; you will receive a push notification because the message is from the Bot.
